President Obama has declared a state of emergency in Rhode Island due to the conditions caused by Hurricane Sandy. This declaration authorizes the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected population. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Emergency protective measures will be funded by the federal government at 75 percent. James N. Russo has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.